    {
      "name": "04 - Coach Advice (POST /api/coach-advice)",
      "description": "Personalised coaching advice endpoint backed by CoachAgent with three tools.\n\nPhase 3 implementation: CoachAgent pre-fetches context from WebSearchTool,\nNutritionCalcTool, and MemoryTool before making a single structured LLM call.\n\nMERN analogy: mastra.getAgent('coachAgent').generate({ topic }) where the\nagent was initialised with tools: { webSearch, nutritionCalc, memory }.\n\nRequest:  { \"topic\": string }   — @NotBlank validated\nResponse: CoachAdvice { summary, actionItems[], weeklyGoal, disclaimer }\n\nBook ref: Chapter 6 — Tool Calling (pre-fetch / augmented context pattern).\nBook ref: Chapter 10 — Third-Party Tools & Integrations (WebSearchTool stub).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /api/coach-advice — happy path",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"topic\": \"omega-3 fatty acids for cardiovascular health\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/coach-advice",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "coach-advice"]
            },
            "description": "Requests personalised coaching advice for a nutrition topic.\n\nCoachAgent will:\n1. Call WebSearchTool.searchWeb(topic)       — supplementary facts\n2. Call NutritionCalcTool.calculateNutrition — macro data\n3. Call MemoryTool.lookupNotes              — user history\n4. Build enriched prompt → Gemini → CoachAdvice\n5. Call MemoryTool.storeMemory              — persist session\n\nExpected response shape: { summary, actionItems[], weeklyGoal, disclaimer }"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', () => {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has all CoachAdvice fields', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('summary');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('actionItems');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('weeklyGoal');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('disclaimer');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('summary is a non-empty string', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.summary).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('actionItems is a non-empty array', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.actionItems).to.be.an('array').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('weeklyGoal is a non-empty string', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.weeklyGoal).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('disclaimer is present', () => {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.disclaimer).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Save last advice topic for chaining",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.summary) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('last_coach_summary', json.summary);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK — example CoachAdvice",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n    \"topic\": \"omega-3 fatty acids for cardiovascular health\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/coach-advice",
                  "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "coach-advice"]
                }
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
              "body": "{\n    \"summary\": \"Omega-3 fatty acids EPA and DHA, found in fatty fish and algae supplements, have strong evidence for reducing triglycerides and supporting cardiovascular health. Aim for 1–2 g EPA+DHA daily from whole-food sources or a high-quality supplement.\",\n    \"actionItems\": [\n        \"Eat 150 g of salmon or mackerel at least 3 times this week\",\n        \"If using supplements, choose a triglyceride-form fish oil with >500 mg EPA+DHA per capsule\",\n        \"Replace refined seed oils (sunflower, corn) with olive oil for cooking\",\n        \"Add 1 tbsp of ground flaxseed to breakfast daily for ALA intake\"\n    ],\n    \"weeklyGoal\": \"Consume at least 3 servings of fatty fish or take a daily 1 g EPA+DHA supplement every day this week.\",\n    \"disclaimer\": \"This advice is for informational purposes only and does not substitute for medical advice from a qualified healthcare professional.\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
